S'Phonto is a simple application that allows you to add text to pictures.\xe2\x98\x85 More than 50 fonts are available.\xe2\x98\x85 You can install other fonts.\xe2\x98\x85 Text size is changeable.\xe2\x98\x85 Text color is changeable.\xe2\x98\x85 Text shodow is changeable.\xe2\x98\x85 Text is rotatable.\xe2\x98\x85 Text stroke color and width is changeable.\xe2\x98\x85 Text background color is changeable.NOTE: Too large image could cause the app to crash. You should enable \'Mediam\' or \'Small\' image size setting.-------------------------------------How to install fonts-------------------------------------To install fonts, place the font files (***ttf or ***.otf) into the fonts folder, /[sdcard]/Phonto/fonts.\'Phonto\' and \'fonts\' folders will be created automatically after Phonto launched.In addition to that, you can install fonts from file management app like ASTRO file manager. 1. Download font file from online. Google "FREE FONT".2. Unzip if you downloaded zip file (***.zip).3. Open font file (***ttf or ***.otf) in Phonto from file management app.Dropbox http://db.tt/4RiIoRb7 allows you to easily share font files between PC and smartphone.- Too many font files might cause the app to crash. You should reduce the number of font files as small as possible.- If you download a font file from online as zip format (***.zip), you need to unzip it.-------------------------------------Ad-Free option-------------------------------------Ad-Free option removes all advertisements from Phonto. If you want to buy this option, please go to "Settings" in Phonto and tap "Ad-Free Option".Recent changes:1.3.0-------------------------------You can now use plain images instead of photos. (In-App Billing)This feature requires Android OS 4.0 (ICS) or higher.1.2.1-------------------------------\xe2\x98\x85 Text background.\xe2\x98\x85 Text stroke.\xe2\x98\x85 Text alignment.\xe2\x98\x85 Ad-Free Option (In-App Billing)'
